    "directions_source_text": "1. clean the kidney and remove the fat 2. cut the kidney into small chunks (2cm or 3/4\") 3. put butter in a casserole dish 4. add kidney, parsley, bay leaf, salt, pepper 5. brown in the casserole for 10 minutes while stirring (don't burn) 6. add 2 glasses of dry white wine 7. add half a glass of water so that the mixture is well-bathed 8. simmer for 35 minutes 9. add about 400g of toasted bread in pieces 10. simmer for another 10 minutes"
